title: Volunteer Wetland Restoration
description:
You and your fellow volunteers will participate in fun, hands-on forest restoration work led by DNDA’s Nature team. Restoration work includes removing invasive plants, planting native species, and mulching new plantings. Specific activities depend on the time of year and restoration progress at each site.

What to bring:

  • Please dress appropriately with long pants, warm and dry layers, closed-toed shoes and rain gear as needed. We work rain or shine!
  • Bring any water you might want during the volunteer event
  • If you have your own pair of work gloves, feel free to bring them. If not, we will have plenty
  • Signed youth waiver form, if under 18

What we provide:

  • Tools
  • Gloves
  • Light snacks
  • Training on restoration activity and safety talk

 

Location: Delridge Wetland Park

Delridge Wetland Park, located on 23rd Ave SW and SW Findlay St, is a project spearheaded by DNDA to protect, restore, preserve and expand the existing wetland to improve water quality in Longfellow Creek, meanwhile developing the space as a public park for all to enjoy. Besides wetland restoration, other plans for the park include the creation of an urban garden, community orchard, as well as developing the space as an outdoor classroom for local students and the community to learn hands-on environmental science and wetland stewardship.

title: Roxhill Community Cleanup
description:
Join DNDA for a morning of park stewardship, nature-based art, and educational activities around Roxhill Bog!

Come to the park to join us for a morning of trail maintenance, trash pickup, and art activities. We’ll also be sharing information about upcoming construction at the park!

What to bring:

  • Please dress appropriately with long pants, warm and dry layers, closed-toed shoes and rain gear as needed. We work rain or shine!
  • Bring any water you might want during the volunteer event
  • If you have your own pair of work gloves, feel free to bring them. If not, we will have plenty
  • Signed youth waiver form, if under 18

What we provide:

  • Tools
  • Gloves
  • Light snacks
  • Training on restoration activity and safety talk

Location: 2850 SW Roxbury St

Driving Directions:

From I-5 or Route 99 (heading north or south)

* Take the West Seattle Bridge exit off either highway.

* From the bridge take the Delridge Way SW/South Seattle Comm. College exit (right hand exit).

* Stay to your left to exit onto Delridge Way SW.

* From Delridge Way SW, turn onto SW Barton Street, heading west

* Turn left onto 29th Ave SW

* Street parking available on either side of the street here and in the park lot before the intersection with SW Cambridge St

* Our staff will meet volunteers south of the bathroom structure near the playground.

Busing Directions: Accessible by Rapid Ride C route and Metro routes 21, 60, 120, 125 and 560
